<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-7859818959850411268'>
<p>
Interesting read, but severely hampered by some very obvious beginner&#39;s misunderstandings about ObjC.<br /><br />- Methods that start with a + are not static, they&#39;re class methods. Ones with a - are instance methods<br />- ObjC does not have named arguments.<br />- In the section where you show how often you declare a property, the first time within the @interface section is not actually declaring the property, but an instance variable.<br /><br />All of these examples kind of show that you don&#39;t completely understand what&#39;s going on.<br /><br />Again, interesting read, but you should do a bit more research on ObjC and the iPhone frameworks before you can really make a solid comparison between them and anything else.
</p>
</dd>
