<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-873053087971689012'>
<p>
Non-managed languages should be a thing of the past, but Objective-C is entrenched inside Apple.<br /><br />There are numerous posts on this forum saying people should stop living in the past and embrace new technologies. Exactly--so I can&#39;t wait for Apple&#39;s engineers to start doing that.<br /><br />It&#39;s been repeatedly shown that memory leaks and the monotony of writing managed code are a huge drain on programmer productivity.<br /><br />Why do something by hand that can be automated? That&#39;s what computers are *for*.<br /><br />It&#39;s no wonder the memory-leak analyzer for Objective-C is better than the one for Android--it has to be because it&#39;s possible to leak memory in Objective-C.<br /><br />I sure hope Android takes off.<br /><br />The killer app would be a tool that inputs Android source code and outputs iphone code.
</p>
</dd>
