<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-3120882804645774172'>
<p>
@Adam Smith  I agree that more experience with XCode would have helped a lot.  Especially wrt opening new windows: By using different key/mouse combinations and All-In-One layout new windows are opened much less often.  When it comes to window management, XCode with the default settings makes it too easy to have a bad experience.<br /><br />@Richard re: cost of phones and development: I&#39;m sure if you already have a plan, then an iPhone costs more, but for me I had to sign up for a plan to do either.  After signing up for a plan I still had to buy the Android developer phone -- so the price comparison works out for me.
</p>
