<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-7209681014717436872'>
<p>
Curious thing .... how Smalltalk has  directly influenced the flow  of certain things.<br />Objective C drew a lot of inspiration and ideas from Smalltalk. On the other hand, Eclipse started it&#39;s life as a Smalltalk IDE. <br />To the folks who think GC is bad and memory management is cool because it is fast, what are you smoking? Why don&#39;t you go program in assembly language? Your programs will be REALLY fast then, no machine cycles need be wasted.  Or perhaps in machine language - 1s and 0s - not a single cycle need be wasted. The problem may be that you live in your own little backwards world and that&#39;s all you know. Sort of like primitive people fighting against advancement of technology.<br />As for the argument that mobile devices are not ready for GC, that&#39;s what ignorant people said in 80s about computers. The solution is to modify GC architectures for mobile phones
</p>
</dd>
